# notify.env.example — copy to ~/.claude/notify.env and fill in (autonomy plan 2.1).
# Read by ~/.claude/hooks/notify-checkpoint.sh. NEVER commit the filled file.
#
# The ntfy topic IS the secret: anyone who knows it can read your pings and send you
# fakes. Generate a long random one and treat it like a password:
#   openssl rand -hex 16
# Then subscribe to that topic in the ntfy app (https://ntfy.sh — iOS/Android/desktop).
#
# With NTFY_TOPIC unset, the hook falls back to a Windows toast (BurntToast), then to
# a .pipeline/notify-log.jsonl line. It never fails a run.
#
# Payload rule (enforced by the hook): pings carry event + feature slug + repo name
# ONLY — never diff content, findings, or report text.

NTFY_TOPIC=
